FBIS4-29702 "dreas119_l_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-119 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 Philippines Cuban Ambassador Found Dead Cuban Ambassador Found Dead BK2106035394 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 21 Jun 94 BK2106035394 Quezon City Radio Filipinas English BFN [Text] Cuba's ambassador to the Philippines, Jose Luis Martin Portal, had been found dead at his Manila home, apparently from cardiac arrest. He was 49. The Philippines' Foreign Office said Portal's body was found on Sunday evening [19 June] by his household staff, who called the police. Portal's wife and children were in Havana, and the envoy was living alone in the exclusive North Forbes Park district in Metro Manila. Police said they found no sign of foul play. Portal assumed his Manila post in October 1990.
